results.name: Strict Moebius function of the multiorder of integer partitions indexed by Heinz numbers.
comment: The Heinz number of an integer partition (y_1,...,y_k) is prime(y_1)*...*prime(y_k).
formula: mu(y) = Sum_{g(t)=y} (-1)^d(t), where the sum is over all strict trees (A273873) whose multiset of leaves is the integer partition y, and d(t) is the number of non-leaf nodes in t.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Feb 07 2018
